				\begin{document}$$\begin{array}{rcl}{\beta }_{0ij} & = & {\gamma }_{00j}+{\mu }_{0ij}\\ {\beta }_{1ij} & = & {\gamma }_{10j}+{\mu }_{1ij}\end{array}.$$\end{document}β0ij=γ00j+μ0ijβ1ij=γ10j+μ1ij.In these expressions, γ00j and γ10j are the mean intercept and slope pooled over all small watersheds within county j, while the residuals μ0ij and μ1ij denote the deviation of the intercept and slope around county-specific mean values, respectively. Finally, Var(μ0ij) = τβ00, Var(μ1ij) = τβ11, and cov (μ0ij, μ1ij) = τβ; these denote variation between Level 2 units.

